-- в”Ђв”Ђ Adaptable в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$Adaptable is a deployment platform that connects to a GitHub repository and automatically builds, deploys, and manages the infrastructure for full-stack applications, including databases, load balancing, and SSL.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$usage-based$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE($q$From 3 dollars per month plus resource usage$q$, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(2022, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE(NULL, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE($q$Denver, Colorado, United States$q$, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$Adaptable.io Review 2026: GitHub-Connected App Deployment Pricing$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$Adaptable.io deploys full-stack apps straight from a GitHub repo, handling databases, load balancing, and SSL automatically. See pricing, features, and FAQs.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$Adaptable, also known as Adaptable.io, is a deployment automation platform founded in 2022 and headquartered in Denver, Colorado. The company describes its product as the easiest way to deploy an application: a developer connects a GitHub repository and Adaptable handles the rest, from building the app to provisioning the infrastructure it needs to run in production. Rather than requiring users to manually configure servers, databases, load balancers, content delivery networks, and SSL and TLS certificates, Adaptable automates that provisioning based on templates tied to the type of application being deployed. Each time a developer pushes new code to their selected branch on GitHub, Adaptable automatically rebuilds the application and updates the live deployment, functioning as a continuous deployment pipeline built directly on top of Git workflows. The platform also supports preview deployments, letting teams designate a development branch that gets its own deployment for testing changes before merging to production. Adaptable is designed to host a wide range of web-based applications, including front-end interfaces, back-end services, and the supporting infrastructure they depend on, positioning it as an alternative to manually wiring together separate hosting, database, and networking providers. App templates handle the specifics of building an application and defining the cloud resources it needs, including serverless containers and managed databases, reducing the DevOps configuration typically required to get a full-stack app into production. Adaptable's pricing combines fixed and usage-based plans. A fixed-price plan starts at 3 dollars per month with a 10-day free trial and no usage charges, subject to resource usage limits per app. A usage-based plan for individual apps starts at 5 dollars per month per app plus resource usage, which includes a 5 dollar resource usage credit. A usage-based organization plan starts at 20 dollars per month per organization plus resource usage, also including a 5 dollar credit and support for up to 3 users. This tiered structure lets solo developers and small teams start cheaply while scaling costs with actual infrastructure consumption as an application grows. Because Adaptable is a smaller, more recently founded company, detailed public information about its employee count, funding, and broader company history is limited compared to larger, more established infrastructure providers.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = 'f4aa26bc-375b-4808-a448-465f4f778755';

