-- в”Ђв”Ђ Addepar в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$Addepar is a cloud-based wealth management platform that aggregates and analyzes portfolio data for registered investment advisors and financial institutions, powering reporting on trillions of dollars in assets.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$custom$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE($q$Custom pricing, contact sales; fees are typically tiered based on assets under management and user licenses$q$, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(2009, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE($q$1,400-plus employees$q$, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE($q$Mountain View, California, United States$q$, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$Addepar Review 2026: Wealth Management Software Pricing and Features$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$Addepar is a data aggregation and portfolio reporting platform for registered investment advisors and wealth managers. See its features, pricing, pros, cons and FAQs.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$Addepar is a cloud-based wealth management software platform founded in 2009 by Joseph Lonsdale, Jason Mirra, and Brittney Mickel, and headquartered in Mountain View, California, with additional offices in New York, London, Pune in India, and Dubai. The company has grown substantially, reporting approximately 1,400 employees as of 2026, up from around 1,000 in 2024, reflecting continued expansion of its team. Addepar specializes in data aggregation, analytics, and portfolio reporting for registered investment advisors, family offices, private banks, and other financial professionals who need a unified view of complex, multi-custodian investment portfolios. The platform pulls together data from disparate custodians, asset classes, and account structures into a single system of record, enabling advisors to analyze performance, exposure, and risk across public securities as well as harder-to-value alternative investments such as private equity, real estate, and hedge funds. Addepar states that its platform is trusted by financial professionals globally and powers reporting on more than 9 trillion dollars in assets across more than 1,400 clients in over 60 countries, positioning it as one of the most widely used data infrastructure platforms in the wealth management industry. Revenue is primarily subscription-based, delivered as software as a service, with tiered pricing that generally scales with the assets under management an advisor or firm manages on the platform, plus the number of user licenses required, supplemented by professional services fees for onboarding, data migration, and customization. Addepar does not publish a public price list, and prospective customers must contact the company directly for a quote tailored to their asset base and use case. Some users have expressed frustration with a pricing structure in which fees rise as assets under management grow but do not automatically decrease proportionally if a client's assets under management later falls, a common point of criticism in reviews of the platform. Addepar has continued to expand its capabilities over time, including enhanced reporting, mobile access, third-party integrations, and analytics aimed at both financial advisors and their end clients. As a company handling highly sensitive financial data at scale, Addepar emphasizes security, data integrity, and analytics designed specifically for the operational realities of registered investment advisors and other regulated wealth management firms.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = '673f3f0e-691b-45d1-8e4a-dfea89115d74';

